Fission Yield of the Tin Isotopes, 2.1 Hr 127-Sn was
Used As an Internal Monitor. The Yield of this Nuclide
Was Calculated from Ratios Between the Yields of 129-Sb
And 127-Sb Obtained by Isolating Antimony at Different
Times After Bombardment Always, However, Ensuring
Complete Decay of 8.8 Min 129-Sn and 4.6 Min 127-Sn.
